    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">540.48 Refugees/4536: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-04T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 4, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3196. Chief Political Division Foreign Office says advices from Denmark indicate
                    local German officials there are being very lax in <pb facs="0371" n="361"
                        xml:id="pg_361"/> carrying out instructions for deportation of Jews.
                    Although final figures are unavailable as many who escaped to Sweden do not
                    arrive in populated spots nearly 3,000 have already escaped to Sweden, i.e.,
                    nearly half of number intended to be deported. Official mentioned above believes
                    that strong campaign from Sweden has affected local German officials in Denmark
                    so that they fear for their personal safety if carrying out instructions too
                    vigorously.</p>
                <p>Swedish Government has followed up its original <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>
                    in Berlin (see Legation’s 3149, September 30, 10 p.m. and 3180, October 2, 10
                        p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d364fn32">Latter not printed.</note>) by requesting
                    that in any case Jewish children be sent to Sweden, stating children could not
                    be cause of trouble in Denmark which is alleged cause for deportations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
